1
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:29,952
=Blemish Flaw=

2
00:01:29,952 --> 00:01:32,704
=Episode 6=

3
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,200
Darker?

4
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:44,560
You watch this stuff?

5
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:46,120
You didn't update.

6
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,879
I have to watch this to kill time.

7
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,719
Yang Zhenghui!

8
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,400
Huang?

9
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,599
Why are you here?

10
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,079
Like you've seen a ghost.

11
00:01:57,439 --> 00:01:58,680
I don't want to see you either.

12
00:02:01,319 --> 00:02:02,400
Is this your girlfriend?

13
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,439
Your taste

14
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:04,439
has changed.

15
00:02:04,519 --> 00:02:05,239
Stop it.

16
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,599
She's just a friend.

17
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,120
Don't worry.

18
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,719
Having a girlfriend

19
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:10,520
is a good thing.

20
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,919
She's got limited mobility.

21
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,039
Take good care of her.

22
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,360
No offense.

23
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,439
You're offending me.

24
00:02:15,599 --> 00:02:16,879
Can you stop it?

25
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,360
What are you worried about?

26
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:19,360
Why so worried?

27
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:20,319
I'm not!

28
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,080
Don't stay here.

29
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:21,879
I'm begging you.

30
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,560
Just leave.

31
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,520
Get out of here.

32
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:23,840
Fine.

33
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,719
Just go, thanks.

34
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:26,319
Don't touch me.

35
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:26,919
Alright.

36
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,840
I'll leave you alone.

37
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:29,520
Wishing you good health.

38
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:32,199
You!

39
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:33,840
Ex-girlfriend?

40
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,800
The one

41
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:39,080
you couldn't find last year?

42
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:40,520
No.

43
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:41,919
The one before that.

44
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:44,000
She doesn't seem

45
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,280
very friendly toward you.

46
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,840
The breakup was messy.

47
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,680
It was years ago.

48
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:50,840
I hadn't started making

49
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,360
videos.

50
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,319
Had no money either.

51
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,639
Even for her birthday,

52
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:54,919
I had to borrow money

53
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,879
to buy her gifts.

54
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,000
Then some guy

55
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:57,800
pursued her.

56
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,000
He was pretty wealthy.

57
00:02:59,080 --> 00:02:59,680
I found it out

58
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:00,840
and we had a huge fight.

59
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:02,879
She cut ties with him.

60
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,000
But soon after,

61
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,879
she dated

62
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,759
another guy.

63
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,400
That guy

64
00:03:06,439 --> 00:03:07,400
was married.

65
00:03:07,759 --> 00:03:08,759
She wasn't right for you.

66
00:03:08,879 --> 00:03:10,000
No need to tolerate her.

67
00:03:13,719 --> 00:03:15,439
Not really.

68
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:17,719
With my conditions then,

69
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,199
no girl was right for me.

70
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,120
But

71
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:27,400
I later made up my mind

72
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:28,240
to quit my job

73
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:30,080
and started making videos.

74
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,840
Are you successful now?

75
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,439
Not yet.

76
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:34,639
But my income is

77
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,800
better than before.

78
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,439
I've already

79
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,360
shared

80
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,080
my story.

81
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:42,800
Now

82
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,599
it's your turn.

83
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,759
I didn't ask you to,

84
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:45,680
but you shared it.

85
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,840
I'm just curious

86
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,319
how your husband managed to

87
00:03:48,319 --> 00:03:49,240
win over a wealthy girl

88
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,120
like you.

89
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:51,319
I can tell you,

90
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,400
but you can't learn it.

91
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,319
Maybe I can.

92
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,439
Try me then.

93
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,000
I need to go to the wet market today.

94
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,000
Go with me.

95
00:03:59,199 --> 00:04:00,800
Maybe I'd tell you on the way.

96
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:01,719
Let's go.

97
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,520
What?

98
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:03,759
You forgot the rules.

99
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,639
Luckily, I kept the clothes

100
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,719
in the trunk.

101
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,600
Or, I couldn't

102
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,720
go with you.

103
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,519
You didn't wash

104
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,240
them?

105
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,240
I only wore them for one day.
Why would I?

106
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,199
You men are really something!

107
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,720
I went on

108
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,120
a road trip with a friend

109
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,560
and had a flat tire on the way.

110
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,680
We two girls

111
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,959
couldn't change the tire.

112
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,120
We called for help

113
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:42,759
but they wouldn't arrive for hours.

114
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,040
We were just waiting.

115
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,720
Then we met my husband

116
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,560
who's taking students for fieldwork.

117
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,319
Great!

118
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,079
What's wrong?

119
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,680
My car broke down. The tire is flat.

120
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,120
Spare tire?

121
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:02,759
Yes.

122
00:05:02,759 --> 00:05:03,480
In the trunk.

123
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,600
But we don't know how.

124
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,120
No problem.

125
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:05,920
Here.

126
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:07,120
Put the sign

127
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:07,839
over there.

128
00:05:07,839 --> 00:05:08,199
Okay.

129
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,079
Get the tools and the spare tire.

130
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:10,839
Let's change it.

131
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:11,319
Alright.

132
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,480
Thank you so much!

133
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:40,839
No need. We're passing by.

134
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,519
No big deal.

135
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:42,944
Professor Zeng, done.

136
00:05:43,199 --> 00:05:43,720
Get in then.

137
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:44,439
Okay.

138
00:05:45,319 --> 00:05:47,279
You're so young to be a professor.

139
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,879
Just an assistant professor.

140
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,120
Are you taking students on a trip?

141
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,040
I'm taking them for fieldwork.

142
00:05:55,319 --> 00:05:56,879
Art Department of Caorong University.

143
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,319
Where are you going?

144
00:05:58,439 --> 00:05:59,000
Maybe join us?

145
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,560
We are just vacationing.

146
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,839
You drive such a nice car,

147
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,680
probably stay in a boutique hotel.

148
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:06,199
When we do fieldwork,

149
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:07,160
usually stay with

150
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:08,000
locals.

151
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:09,079
You two city girls

152
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,240
couldn't stand it.

153
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,000
Okay. Enjoy your trip.

154
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,839
I'm leaving.

155
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,480
I'm Zeng Jie.

156
00:06:33,319 --> 00:06:35,000
What car did you drive?

157
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,480
Cayenne.

158
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,600
Remember what car

159
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:40,680
that rich lady drove?

160
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:41,600
Yes, yes.

161
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,759
We circled the car

162
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:43,759
a few times

163
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:45,839
and saw it clearly. A Porsche.

164
00:06:46,519 --> 00:06:48,160
Do you have a Porsche sports car?

165
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,040
I've never liked sports cars.

166
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:52,360
I prefer taller vehicles

167
00:06:52,399 --> 00:06:53,199
with better views.

168
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,639
So you and your husband

169
00:06:56,639 --> 00:06:58,079
just started dating then?

170
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,680
(Zeng Jie's Moments)
Not bad.

171
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,920
He's your type,
dressing decent but wild inside.

172
00:07:04,279 --> 00:07:06,120
What did you say?

173
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,040
Look,

174
00:07:07,319 --> 00:07:08,480
he's an artist.

175
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,319
His Moments is

176
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,480
filled with ceramics.

177
00:07:11,079 --> 00:07:12,319
I never realized

178
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,959
ceramics could be so beautiful.

179
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:15,439
What now?

180
00:07:16,079 --> 00:07:17,120
You fancy him.

181
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,319
Now you even like

182
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:19,839
what he likes?

183
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,199
He's talented.

184
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:22,560
(Zeng Jie's Profile)
He's won awards.

185
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,439
At his age,

186
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,639
he's already a professor.

187
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,240
Miss Bai,

188
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,519
make your move now,

189
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,279
or

190
00:07:29,399 --> 00:07:30,519
other beauties might

191
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,240
beat you to it.

192
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:32,199
Heard me?

193
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,319
Stop it. Get in the car.

194
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,160
Soon after my birthday,

195
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,560
he saw my post

196
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:39,879
and sent me a gift.

197
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,360
I received a gift,

198
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:42,399
very special.

199
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,480
Just an ordinary piece of work.

200
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,360
This is a hairpin, right?

201
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,360
You made this?

202
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:50,120
Yes.

203
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,240
You have everything.

204
00:07:51,639 --> 00:07:52,959
Designer bags, jewelry.

205
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,959
You've got all that.

206
00:07:54,279 --> 00:07:55,240
So I made

207
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,759
this thing for you.

208
00:07:57,439 --> 00:07:58,399
I really like it.

209
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,879
Since childhood,

210
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:00,759
no one ever

211
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,959
made anything for me.

212
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,680
Let alone something this special.

213
00:08:04,199 --> 00:08:05,439
You even engraved a poem?

214
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,920
What does it say?

215
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,480
I yearn to send a letter to my beloved.

216
00:08:10,759 --> 00:08:14,360
But mountains stretch, rivers flow.
I have no idea where my beloved is.

217
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,160
Why can't I

218
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,000
recognize it?

219
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,040
In ancient script.

220
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,439
Just knowing the meaning.

221
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:21,759
What does that mean?

222
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:23,959
(I found a poetry.)

223
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,600
Being young and charming
as plum blossoms.

224
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,480
I wear a flower hairpin,
betrothed to you.

225
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:31,079
This man is really something.

226
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,959
Perhaps.

227
00:08:32,639 --> 00:08:34,519
Anyway, I was quite moved,

228
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,559
thinking he's really thoughtful.

229
00:08:39,879 --> 00:08:40,679
True.

230
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,320
Whatever he does,

231
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,320
he's always this thoughtful.

232
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,759
Let me tell you.

233
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,039
This fish is so fresh.

234
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,919
All picked this morning.

235
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,480
I fear you wouldn't come today.

236
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:55,279
Thanks.

237
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,080
Take care.

238
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,519
That vendor knows you well.

239
00:08:58,679 --> 00:09:00,360
You love fish?

240
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,000
I'm so noticeable.

241
00:09:02,159 --> 00:09:02,799
Coming twice,

242
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:03,960
and they all remember me.

243
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,679
I don't like fish.

244
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,840
But my husband does.

245
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,480
Despite all this,

246
00:09:08,519 --> 00:09:09,519
you still cook at home?

247
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,559
Despite all this,

248
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:12,080
I can only cook at home.

249
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:13,120
Besides,

250
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:14,759
I want to do something.

251
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:16,919
As usual?

252
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,080
Pork belly, a bit leaner.

253
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,639
Pork liver and lungs,

254
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,120
a bit of each.

255
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:26,000
You don't seem like eating these.

256
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,519
He likes pork belly.

257
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,399
Liver and lung soup

258
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,200
are good for him.

259
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,120
He often stays up late.

260
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:31,919
You're such a devoted wife.

261
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,200
All done.

262
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,720
Next, let's get some greens?

263
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:39,320
What do you like to eat?

264
00:09:39,639 --> 00:09:40,600
There's

265
00:09:40,679 --> 00:09:41,519
a supermarket

266
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:42,440
by the market entrance.

267
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,879
They sell excellent steaks

268
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:44,639
and bread.

269
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,559
(Steak)
It's pricey.

270
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:49,200
With higher meat grade.

271
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,559
Should I drive you back to cafÃ©

272
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,559
or home?

273
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,440
Home.

274
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:56,120
My husband is working late.

275
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,120
Can't pick me up.

276
00:09:57,559 --> 00:09:58,080
Okay.

277
00:10:02,759 --> 00:10:04,360
Your husband is really lucky.

278
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,759
You treat him so well.

279
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:08,320
What's special about
shopping and cooking?

280
00:10:08,519 --> 00:10:10,320
Aren't all wives doing so?

281
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:11,360
Besides,

282
00:10:11,559 --> 00:10:12,799
I'm disabled now.

283
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,240
Is it lucky?

284
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,679
You weren't disabled before.

285
00:10:15,799 --> 00:10:17,320
And you'll recover.

286
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:26,120
Let me take you home.

287
00:10:26,519 --> 00:10:27,600
No need. It's close enough.

288
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,000
I'll go back myself.

289
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,200
I'm dressed like this.

290
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,480
Don't worry.

291
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,559
I'm not worrying.

292
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:34,519
I can go back on my own.

293
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:35,919
You've helped me a lot.

294
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,519
Thank you.

295
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,399
Alright.

296
00:10:37,519 --> 00:10:38,399
Be careful then.

297
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:39,840
Wash the clothes.

298
00:11:37,799 --> 00:11:38,440
Zeng Jie.

299
00:11:38,879 --> 00:11:40,360
Before I discharge,

300
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,960
